Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and
dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce}
into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon},
@dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef. Cook chicken until cooked through,
> 3-5 minutes per side; or cook pork to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

While beef cooks, toss broccoli on a second baking sheet with a large drizzle
of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium heat. Add
shallot; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}; simmer until slightly reduced,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @cherry jam{1} and 1⁄3 cup water (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Cook until
thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt, pepper, and up to @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}
(1 tsp for 4) to taste.

Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

Return beef to pan; turn to coat in sauce.

Divide beef, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Top beef with any remaining
sauce and serve.